---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
---
<Layout
  title="About PromptAndGo — Built for Asia, Built for Every Language"
  description="PromptAndGo was built because generic AI prompts miss the cultural, linguistic, and business nuances that matter across Asia. Learn the story."
>
  <section class="container py-16 md:py-24 max-w-3xl">
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight">About PromptAndGo</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-muted-foreground">Built for Asia. Built for every language. Built to ship work, not demos.</p>

    <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert mt-10 max-w-none">
      <h2>The problem we saw</h2>
      <p>
        Most "best AI prompts" lists are written for North American knowledge work. They don't ask whether
        you need <em>keigo</em> for Japanese clients, whether your Korean cold email opens with the right honorific,
        or whether your Mandarin marketing copy lands as polite or pushy. The result: AI output that looks
        fluent but feels off — and a lot of human time spent fixing it.
      </p>

      <h2>Our approach</h2>
      <p>
        We curate, test, and optimize prompts with cultural and linguistic context built in. Each prompt
        in our library has been run against the major AI platforms — ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Mistral, Grok —
        and tuned for the platforms our users actually use, including Asia-specific deployments.
      </p>

      <h2>Who we serve</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Marketers and content teams localizing across multiple Asian markets</li>
        <li>Customer support orgs handling tickets in 5+ languages</li>
        <li>Founders and small businesses standing up AI workflows without a research team</li>
        <li>Educators and certification candidates building AI fluency</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Where we're going</h2>
      <p>
        More languages, deeper market context (we're rolling out market insights for Malaysia, Indonesia,
        Vietnam, Australia next), and direct integrations with the AI platforms our users live in.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3">
      <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-primary text-primary-foreground px-6 py-3 font-semibold">Get in touch</a>
      <a href="/library" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg border border-border px-6 py-3 font-semibold">Browse prompts</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
